The paper deals with the distributed computational complexity of LCL problems, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC). The fact that the problem is defined on a path suggests that it may also be relevant to the study of graph algorithms, which falls under cs.DS. The use of complexity theory and algorithmic analysis suggests that it may also be relevant to cs.CC. The paper also discusses information theory and communication complexity, which are topics in cs.IT. Finally, the paper presents an algorithm for determining the distributed computational complexity of LCL problems, which may be of interest to researchers in machine learning and optimization, falling under cs.LG.
